checkboxtest: Check box to exclude this case from analytics
archive_message: WARNING: This action is not reversible!
organizationName: organization name (only show when push message)
invalidphonenumber: Invalid phone number. Please use format +49xxxxxxxxxx or 0xxxxxxxxxx (where x are digits, total min. 9 digits, max. 15 digits)
editcasewarning: Warning: the updated data will automatically be transmitted to the pass within 2min. There is no need to send a new SMS.
enterTextForYourPushMessage: Enter text for your push message
reset_message: The timer of this cass will be restarted
publish_message: WARNING: If any changes exist, they will be published to all passes
headerTooltip: Remains visible in the pass overview. Use this for key information that allows the user to identify and select the pass.
primaryTooltip: Use this for most prominent, short content.
secondaryTooltip: Use this for the main content on the front side.
auxiliaryTooltip: Use this for additional content on the front side.
backTooltip: Use this for content sections on the back side. Back-fields can hold long text content, including paragraphs and links. A pass can contain an unlimited number of back-fields
descriptionTooltip: Brief description of the pass, is displayed at the top of the back side.
logoTextTooltip: Branding text, is displayed next to the logo.
barcodeMessageTooltip: Text to be displayed as QR Code so that it can be scanned from the front side of the pass. Can be used for URLs or IDs etc.
associatedStoreIdentifiersTooltip: App-Store-ID of the app that should be linked on the pass.
name: name
paramDescriptionTooltip: Adding a parameter will allow individualized data to be displayed in pass
paramNameTooltip: Name of parameter to describe parameter. Each name must be unique, as the pass can only recognized the parameter through it’s name
paramTypeTooltip: Type of parameter determines the input type for validation. Currently offering: text, email, phone number, date
paramRequireTooltip: Check this if parameter is a required field when editing case data
paramVisibleTooltip: Check this if the parameter to be visible when editing base content or case data, uncheck if it's used for workflow state only.
removeParamMessage: WARNING: This will remove all parameters which appears in the base. This action is not reversible.
relevantDateTooltip: Date and time when the pass becomes relevant. For example, the start time of a movie.
maxDistanceTooltip: Maximum distance in meters from a relevant latitude and longitude that the pass is relevant. This number is compared to the pass’s default distance and the smaller value is used.
paramDisplayNameTooltip: This name will be shown in case creation
workflowEmptyText: This base has no workflow yet
warningURLWithoutLegal: This is the URL without legal consent page.
warningQRWithoutLegal: This is the QR code without legal consent page.
Name: Name
passwordLengthMustBe: (*) Password length must be between 8 - 128 characters
